Good (relative term) Laptop Omarchy Install Steps =========================================================================================================================================
 install through ventoy ISO
- connect to internet
iwctl
device wlan0 set-property Powered off
device wlan0 set-property Powered on
station wlan0 scan
station wlan0 get-networks
station wlan0 connect
D7ED9E936EDF
'quit' 
- run updater

- replace default keybindings
https://github.com/evilusean/Pysean/blob/main/Arch.BTW/Hyprland/OMarchy-OMArchSean/OmArchSean-Keybindings

- Mount Drives :
sudo pacman -S gnome-disk-utility
search 'disks' to open gnome disk utility
add drives, 'Edit Mount Options' -> Switch off 'User Session Defaults' -> 'Mount at system startup' -> Identify As '/dev/sdb2' + Mountpoint (Fstab will be updated)

- add scripts (~/Scripts/system)
https://github.com/evilusean/Pysean/blob/main/Arch.BTW/Hyprland/OMarchy-OMArchSean/launch_venv.sh
https://github.com/evilusean/Pysean/blob/main/Arch.BTW/Hyprland/OMarchy-OMArchSean/lock_and_suspend.sh
https://github.com/evilusean/Pysean/blob/main/Arch.BTW/Hyprland/OMarchy-OMArchSean/ocr_to_clipboard.sh
https://github.com/evilusean/Pysean/blob/main/Arch.BTW/Hyprland/OMarchy-OMArchSean/ocr_to_clipboard_jpn.sh
https://github.com/evilusean/Pysean/blob/main/Arch.BTW/Hyprland/OMarchy-OMArchSean/record.sh
https://github.com/evilusean/Pysean/blob/main/Arch.BTW/Hyprland/OMarchy-OMArchSean/zoom.sh

-fix monitors
'super' + 'space' -> 'setup' -> monitors -> :
.conf/hypr/monitors.conf
# set gdk_scale to 1 for correct sizing on 1080p displays
env = gdk_scale,1
# HDMI-A-1 (ViewSonic) is the external screen, positioned on the LEFT (starts at 0x0)
monitor=HDMI-A-1, 1920x1080@60, 0x0, 1
# eDP-1 (built-in) is the current active screen, positioned on the RIGHT (starts at 1920x0)
monitor=eDP-1, 1920x1080@60, 1920x0, 1

- fix graphics
sudo pacman -S nvidia-dkms nvidia-utils nvidia-settings nvidia-prime opencl-nvidia switcheroo-control nvidia
sudo pacman -S vulkan-icd-loader package
sudo pacman -S lib32-vulkan-icd-loader
sudo pacman -S vulkan-intel
sudo pacman -S lib32-vulkan-intel
sudo pacman -S nvidia-utils
sudo pacman -S lib32-nvidia-utils
sudo pacman -S vulkan-nouveau
sudo pacman -S lib32-vulkan-nouveau
sudo pacman -S vulkan-tools
sudo pacman -S lib32-gnutls

- install steam
sudo pacman -S steam
sudo pacman -S wine wine-mono wine-gecko winetricks
- Move OW2 Shaders
mkdir -p ~/Games/Overwatch_ShaderCache
ln -s ~/Games/Overwatch_ShaderCache /mnt/sdb5/SteamLibrary/steamapps/shadercache
-install lutris
sudo pacman -S lutris
select the executable, select the wine prefix(the one that 'drive_c' is in), select the wine version, and set the default graphics card

- install yay packages
yay -S github-desktop-bin --noconfirm
yay -S anki-bin
yay -S librewolf-bin
yay -S kiro-bin
yay -S warp-terminal

-install packages

-install fonts
sudo pacman -S noto-fonts-cjk noto-fonts-emoji noto-fonts # installs A Japanese capable font
yay -S ttf-freefont ttf-ms-fonts ttf-linux-libertine ttf-dejavu ttf-inconsolata ttf-ubuntu-font-family
-add Japanese keyboard 
sudo pacman -S fcitx5 fcitx5-mozc fcitx5-gtk fcitx5-qt fcitx5-configtool 
'fcitx5-configtool' #after install, run this, add mozc from the 
Go to the "Input Method" tab.
At the bottom left, uncheck "Only Show Current Language". This is crucial, as Mozc is Japanese and your system might be set to English.
In the left pane (Available Input Methods), search for "Mozc".
Select "Mozc" and click the + button (or the right arrow icon) to move it to the "Active Input Methods" list on the right.

-anki setup
sudo pacman -S mpv
mkdir -p ~/.local/share/Anki2
rm -rf ~/.local/share/Anki2/User\ 1
ln -s /mnt/sdb4/Anki/BackupProfile/User\ 1 ~/.local/share/Anki2/User\ 1

-Github Setup
clone repos to ~/Documents/Github/<repo>

-obsidian setup
-syncthing setup
sudo pacman -S syncthing
systemctl --user enable syncthing.service
systemctl --user start syncthing.service
http://localhost:8384/
'Add Remote Device' -> Nearby Devices (have both machines with page open)
'Add Folder' -> Share Folder with device (Obsidian)





















